26/05/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The main international airport in Skopje was closed for an hour Thursday (25 May) due to a phoned-in bomb threat. A special anti-terrorist unit checked the premises and determined the threat was false, police spokesman Borce Pesevski told reporters. Nevertheless, police presence was boosted. (Makfax, Mia, Mediafax - 25/05/06)
